    "text": "Attention-based Multiple Instance Learning aggregators in medical imaging are prone to attention concentration, leading to overconfident and unstable predictions.",
    "topic": "Attention concentration in MIL aggregators"
  },
  {
    "text": "A tailored attention mechanism can retrieve both detailed short-term context and compressed long-term context, reducing inference latency and GPU memory usage.",
    "topic": "Tailored attention mechanism benefits"
  },
  {
    "text": "Weighted Attention Mechanisms (WAMs) must balance efficient inference using recent observations against the cost of retaining long historical context.",
    "topic": "Balancing WAMs for recent vs long-term context"
  }
